WEBVTT

00:05.214 --> 00:10.926
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:11.011 --> 00:14.424
<i>YOU UNLOCK THIS DOOR
WITH THE KEY OF IMAGINATION.</i>

00:14.515 --> 00:16.426
<i>BEYOND IT
IS ANOTHER DIMENSION--</i>

00:16.517 --> 00:18.929
<i>A DIMENSION OF SOUND,</i>

00:19.019 --> 00:20.760
<i>A DIMENSION OF SIGHT,</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:22.936
<i>A DIMENSION OF MIND.</i>

00:23.023 --> 00:25.765
<i>YOU'RE MOVING INTO A LAND
OF BOTH SHADOW AND SUBSTANCE,</i>

00:25.859 --> 00:27.441
<i>OF THINGS AND IDEAS.</i>

00:27.528 --> 00:29.610
<i>YOU'VE JUST
CROSSED OVER INTO...</i>

00:29.696 --> 00:31.687
<i>THE TWILIGHT ZONE.</i>

00:46.672 --> 00:48.538
<i>[meows]</i>

00:48.632 --> 00:53.126
Man: THE ECONOMY OF OUR WORLD,
NOW, THEN, AND FOREVER,

00:53.220 --> 00:56.804
HAVE ALWAYS FOUND

00:56.890 --> 01:02.806
THE INSIDIOUS BREED
OF INTERNATIONAL BANKERS.

01:02.896 --> 01:06.139
THESE ARE THE WORSHIPPERS
OF THE PURSE.

01:06.233 --> 01:08.144
<i>[laughs]</i>

01:08.235 --> 01:12.820
THEIR RELIGION
IS MONETARY GAIN.

01:12.906 --> 01:15.614
THEIR SHRINE IS GOLD.

01:15.701 --> 01:18.068
THEIR LOYALTIES, FIRST,

01:18.120 --> 01:19.986
FOREMOST, AND PRIMARILY,

01:20.080 --> 01:21.912
DEAL WITH MONEY.

01:21.999 --> 01:24.240
WHAT'S WRONG WITH THAT?

01:24.334 --> 01:27.747
EXAMINE THE PHENOMENON
OF FOREIGN CONTROL.

01:27.796 --> 01:29.753
YOU EXAMINE IT,

01:29.798 --> 01:33.257
AND YOU WILL NOTE
WITH ABSOLUTE CLARITY

01:33.302 --> 01:39.139
THAT THE LINES LEAD
DIRECTLY TO PALESTINE!

01:39.224 --> 01:43.593
THEY LEAD DIRECTLY TO AFRICA!

01:43.645 --> 01:45.602
THEY LEAD DIRECTLY...

01:45.647 --> 01:50.266
TO THE VATICAN!

01:50.360 --> 01:52.271
UH, UM...

01:52.362 --> 01:54.273
SO, SO, THERE WE ARE!

01:54.364 --> 01:55.570
THERE IT IS!

01:55.657 --> 01:57.273
THERE IS A CONSPIRACY!

01:57.367 --> 02:00.905
THERE'S A INSIDIOUS,
ENVELOPING CONSPIRACY!

02:00.996 --> 02:05.456
A CONSPIRACY PERSONIFIED
BY THE YELLOW MAN...

02:05.500 --> 02:08.288
BY THE BLACK MAN...

02:08.377 --> 02:10.836
AND BY FOREIGNERS
WHO COME IN

02:10.922 --> 02:14.381
AND INFILTRATE
INTO OUR ECONOMIC STRUCTURE.

02:14.468 --> 02:17.301
OH, THERE'LL COME A MORNING,
YES, THERE WILL,

02:17.346 --> 02:19.838
THERE WILL COME A MORNING

02:19.931 --> 02:22.468
WHEN THESE MEN
HAVE TAKEN OVER YOUR HOME,

02:22.559 --> 02:24.391
THEY'VE TAKEN OVER
YOUR DAUGHTERS...

02:24.478 --> 02:27.220
AND THEY'LL BE SITTING
RIGHT THERE ON YOUR DOORSTEP.

02:27.314 --> 02:29.476
IF ANYBODY'S
SITTING ON YOUR DOORSTEP, BUDDY,

02:29.566 --> 02:31.148
HE'S A MAN IN A WHITE COAT.

02:31.234 --> 02:32.770
AND YOU BETTER
JUST GO WITH HIM, QUIETLY.

02:32.861 --> 02:35.148
YOU THINK THAT'S FUNNY,
DON'T YOU?

02:35.238 --> 02:38.526
YOU THINK IT'S FUNNY
YOUR COUNTRY CAN BE SOLD OUT.

02:38.617 --> 02:42.201
THAT THEY CAN SELL OUT YOUR FLAG
AND YOUR BIRTH RIGHTS.

02:42.287 --> 02:44.073
THAT'S FUNNY, HUH?!

02:44.164 --> 02:45.450
WELL, MAYBE YOU OUGHTA
DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT, PUNK.

02:45.540 --> 02:47.497
YOU'RE SUCH A BIG TIGER,

02:47.584 --> 02:49.416
WHY DON'T YOU COME DOWN HERE
AND DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT?

02:49.503 --> 02:52.495
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING
RIGHT NOW.

02:52.547 --> 02:56.165
SOMEDAY THIS COUNTRY'S
GOING TO WAKE UP.

02:56.259 --> 02:58.341
AND WHEN THEY FIND OUT
HOW IZZY SOLD THEM OUT,

02:58.428 --> 03:01.011
AND HOW RASTUS SOLD THEM OUT
AND HOW PANCHO SOLD THEM OUT,

03:01.056 --> 03:03.343
THEY'RE GOING TO MAKE UP A LIST

03:03.392 --> 03:05.850
OF ALL THE PEOPLE
THAT GET PAID BACK.

03:05.936 --> 03:07.927
AND YOU KNOW WHERE YOU'LL BE?
RIGHT ON THE TOP OF THAT LIST!

03:08.021 --> 03:09.887
RIGHT ON THE TOP!

03:11.400 --> 03:14.518
<i>[jeering laughter]</i>

03:14.611 --> 03:16.397
Speaken
COME HERE, I'LL FIX...

03:22.202 --> 03:24.193
Man: COME HERE! COME HERE!

03:34.673 --> 03:36.414
WHAT'S THE MATTER, PUNK?

03:36.508 --> 03:37.714
NO MORE BIG SPEECHES?

03:37.759 --> 03:39.466
NO MORE BIG TALK, HUH?

03:39.553 --> 03:41.760
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE GONNA SEE
WHEN YOU GET HOME

03:41.847 --> 03:43.429
AND LOOK IN THE MIRROR TONIGHT?

03:43.515 --> 03:45.882
A SCRAWNY LITTLE KOOK
WITH A BIG MOUTH.

03:45.976 --> 03:48.559
A BIG HATER SO LONG AS YOU GOT
A COUPLE OF PUNKS

03:48.603 --> 03:50.765
STANDING IN FRONT OF YA.

03:50.856 --> 03:52.392
<i>[sirens wailing]</i>

03:52.441 --> 03:54.478
<i>[horns honking]</i>

04:06.663 --> 04:08.574
PROBLEMS, FELLAS, HUH?

04:08.623 --> 04:13.117
THE COMMUNISTS,
THE COMMUNISTS DID THIS.

04:13.211 --> 04:14.463
WHICH ONES?

04:17.673 --> 04:20.541
ALL OF 'EM,
ALL OF 'EM ARE COMMUNISTS.

04:23.680 --> 04:25.591
WHAT ABOUT
SOME NAMES, JACK?

04:25.682 --> 04:28.265
IF YOU PRESS CHARGES,
WE'LL NEED NAMES.

04:28.310 --> 04:31.268
JUST FORGET ABOUT IT.
WE CAN HANDLE THIS OURSELVES.

04:31.354 --> 04:33.766
YOU NEED MEDICAL ATTENTION?

04:33.857 --> 04:35.768
WE DON'T NEED ANY.

04:35.859 --> 04:37.475
OKAY, JACK.

04:39.780 --> 04:41.487
HEY, JACK.

04:41.573 --> 04:44.281
YOU FORGOT YOUR, UM,

04:44.367 --> 04:45.983
YOUR FLAG.

04:51.208 --> 04:53.119
THERE'LL COME A DAY
WHEN GUYS LIKE YOU

04:53.210 --> 04:55.702
WILL CRAWL ON YOUR BELLY
JUST TO SALUTE THIS.

04:55.796 --> 04:57.002
THERE'LL COME A DAY.

04:57.088 --> 04:59.125
LET ME KNOW THE DATE, JACK.

04:59.216 --> 05:01.457
THAT MORNING,
I'LL CUT MY WRISTS.

05:20.320 --> 05:21.731
HEY, PETE.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.654
PETE, I'M GLAD YOU'RE OKAY.

05:23.740 --> 05:26.357
BOY, THERE MUST'VE BEEN
EIGHT, TEN GUYS ON TOP OF ME.

05:27.953 --> 05:29.660
I HAD ALL I COULD DO
TO GET AWAY.

05:29.746 --> 05:31.737
YOU GET A MEAN CROWD, PETE.

05:31.832 --> 05:34.870
GET A HOT NIGHT, YOU GET A MEAN OROVVD.
I TOLD YOU GUYS THAT.

05:34.960 --> 05:36.576
EVERY TIME
YOU GET A HOT NIGHT,

05:36.670 --> 05:38.160
YOU GET A COUPLE OF
STIFFS IN THE CROWD

05:38.213 --> 05:39.829
AND THEY SWING AT
ALL THE WRONG WAY.

05:39.881 --> 05:41.872
REMEMBER WHEN I WAS
TELLING YOU THAT?

05:41.967 --> 05:44.004
REMEMBER HOW I WAS TELLING YOU
EVERY TIME YOU GET A HOT NIGHT.

05:44.094 --> 05:46.176
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S DONE. IT'S DONE.

05:47.973 --> 05:50.180
SURE, PETE, SURE.

05:50.267 --> 05:52.258
WHY?

05:52.352 --> 05:55.720
I TRIED SO HARD.

05:57.774 --> 06:00.186
I TRIED SO HARD
OUT THERE TONIGHT, I...

06:03.113 --> 06:05.571
I COULDN'T...GET THROUGH.

06:05.657 --> 06:07.864
I COULDN'T GET THROUGH
TO ANY OF THEM.

06:11.788 --> 06:13.574
I KNEW WHAT
I HAD TO SAY TO THEM,

06:13.665 --> 06:15.827
I KNEVV VVHAT I HAD TO TELL
THEM, AND I JUST COULD...

06:15.917 --> 06:17.703
I COULDN'T.

06:17.794 --> 06:20.536
I COULDN'T GET IT OUT.

06:20.589 --> 06:22.546
I COULDN'T FIND THE WORDS.

06:22.591 --> 06:27.131
SOMEDAY, THEY'RE GOING
TO HAVE TO LISTEN.

06:27.220 --> 06:29.382
SOMEDAY THEY'RE GONNA CHEER!

06:29.431 --> 06:31.217
SOMEDAY THEY WILL, PETE.

06:31.266 --> 06:32.472
THEY WILL.

06:43.612 --> 06:47.321
<i>PORTRAIT OF A BUSH-LEAGUE
FUHRER NAMED PETER I/OLL/I/IER.</i>

06:47.407 --> 06:50.741
<i>A SPARSE LITTLE MAN
WHO FEEDS OFF HIS SELF-DELUSIONS</i>

06:50.827 --> 06:52.818
<i>AND FINDS HIMSELF
PERPETUALLY HUNGRY</i>

06:52.913 --> 06:54.745
<i>FOR WANT OF GREATNESS
IN HIS DIET.</i>

06:54.789 --> 06:57.247
AND LIKE SOME GOOSE-STEPPING
PREDECESSORS,

06:57.334 --> 07:00.167
HE SEARCHES FOR SOMETHING
TO EXPLAIN HIS HUNGER

07:00.253 --> 07:03.962
AND TO RATIONALIZE WHY A WORLD
PASSES HIM BY WITHOUT SALUTING.

07:04.049 --> 07:07.337
THE SOMETHING HE LOOKS FOR,
AND FINDS, IS IN A SEWER.

07:07.427 --> 07:09.759
IN HIS OWN TWISTED
AND DISTORTED LEXICON,

07:09.846 --> 07:12.338
HE CALLS IT
FAITH, STRENGTH, TRUTH.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.343
BUT IN JUST A MOMENT
PETER VOLLMER

07:14.434 --> 07:17.347
WILL PLY HIS TRADE
ON ANOTHER KIND OF CORNER...

07:17.437 --> 07:20.350
A STRANGE INTERSECTION
IN A SHADOWLAND CALLED

07:20.440 --> 07:21.851
THE TWILIGHT ZONE.

07:56.309 --> 08:01.304
<i>[cello playiflQ]</i>

08:37.225 --> 08:39.683
<i>[in German accent]:
WASH YOUR FACE.</i>

08:54.367 --> 08:55.983
[sighs]

09:01.750 --> 09:03.707
IT'S NOT A MORTAL WOUND.

09:03.752 --> 09:05.789
I THINK YOU'LL SURVIVE.

09:05.879 --> 09:09.463
WHEN YOU GET HOME,
PUT SOME IODINE ON IT.

09:09.549 --> 09:11.540
WANT A CUP OF COFFEE?

09:11.593 --> 09:12.799
A DRINK?

09:12.886 --> 09:15.218
MAY I HAVE A DRINK, ERNST?

09:15.263 --> 09:17.379
I HAVE WINE, YOU WANT SOME?

09:48.797 --> 09:51.915
ONE S/PS WINE, PETER.
THIS IS NOT MEDICINE.

09:52.008 --> 09:54.340
WELL, I'LL KEEP THAT
IN MIND FOR NEXT TIME.

09:54.427 --> 09:56.759
FOR THE NEXT TIME?

09:56.805 --> 09:59.513
JUST HOW MANY NEXT TIMES
DO SUPPOSE A HUMAN BEING HAS

09:59.599 --> 10:01.135
IN THE SCHEME OF THINGS?

10:01.226 --> 10:03.092
DON'T LECTURE ME, ERNST.

10:03.186 --> 10:05.427
I'M SICK AND I'M TIRED,
AND I DON'T NEED TO BE LECTURED.

10:19.619 --> 10:21.951
CAN I STAY HERE TONIGHT?

10:22.038 --> 10:25.451
IT REMAINS HERE
FOR YOU, AS USUAL.

10:25.500 --> 10:28.367
YOU'RE A GOOD FRIEND, ERNST.

10:28.461 --> 10:32.455
YOU'RE A GOOD FRIEND.

10:32.549 --> 10:34.290
A <i>MAN DOES</i>
WHAT <i>HE BEL/EVES</i> IN.

10:34.342 --> 10:36.379
A MAN USUALLY DOES.

10:36.469 --> 10:38.210
WELL, I BELIEVE CERTAIN THINGS.

10:38.304 --> 10:40.136
IS THAT A FACT?

10:40.181 --> 10:42.388
YES, WELL,
WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE

10:42.475 --> 10:45.467
IF WE DON'T THINK ALIKE
ABOUT THE SAME THINGS?

10:45.562 --> 10:47.052
I MEAN, WE'RE FRIENDS.

10:47.147 --> 10:51.061
YOU'VE KNOWN ME
SINCE I WAS A KID.

10:51.151 --> 10:52.687
[sighs deeply]

10:52.777 --> 10:55.735
AND WHEN YOU WERE
A LITTLE KID, PETER,

10:55.822 --> 11:01.408
AND I USED TO FIND YOU CRYING
AT MY DOOR LATE AT NIGHT...

11:01.494 --> 11:03.405
I COULD PITY YOU THEN.

11:03.496 --> 11:04.998
AND NOW?

11:05.081 --> 11:06.822
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

11:06.875 --> 11:10.084
NOW YOU PEDDLE HATE
ON STREET CORNERS

11:10.170 --> 11:12.081
AS IF IT WERE POPCORN.

11:12.172 --> 11:14.914
IT'S NOT HATE, IT'S, UH,
IT'S A POINT OF VIEW,

11:15.008 --> 11:16.339
IT'S A PHILOSOPHY.

11:16.426 --> 11:19.418
AH, I KNOW THE PHILOSOPHY.

11:19.512 --> 11:22.220
I KNOW IT QUITE WELL.

11:22.307 --> 11:26.221
NINE YEARS IN A PLACE
CALLED DACHAU.

11:26.311 --> 11:29.224
DO YOU KNOW WHO PUT ME THERE?

11:29.314 --> 11:31.021
PETER VOLLMER.

11:31.107 --> 11:32.939
A LOT OF PETER VOLLMERS.

11:33.026 --> 11:34.937
FRUSTRATED MEN...

11:35.028 --> 11:36.393
SICK MEN...

11:36.487 --> 11:37.943
ANGRY MEN.

11:38.031 --> 11:40.238
BUT THE RESULT,

11:40.325 --> 11:42.032
THE EFFECT--

11:42.118 --> 11:43.734
NEVER MIND THE CAUSE--

11:45.914 --> 11:50.329
12 MILLION BODIES
IN SHALLOW GRAVES.

11:52.128 --> 11:53.914
AND IT ALL STARTED

11:54.005 --> 11:58.124
WITH YOUNG MEN IN UNIFORM
TALKING ON STREET CORNERS.

11:58.218 --> 12:01.631
YOU LET ME COME HERE.

12:01.721 --> 12:04.713
<i>YOU LET ME COME HERE',
YOU NEVER SENT ME AWAY.</i>

12:04.807 --> 12:09.643
NO, I NEVER DID.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.345
I NEVER DO.

12:13.942 --> 12:17.981
THAT'S THE WEAKNESS YOU SCREAM
ABOUT ON YOUR STREET CORNERS.

12:18.071 --> 12:21.860
SENTIMENTALITY, SOFTNESS,

12:21.950 --> 12:25.568
THE WEAKNESS THAT MAKES A MAN
HIS BROTHER'S KEEPER.

12:27.538 --> 12:32.078
OH, I MUST BE ONE OF THE WORST
OF YOUR CRIMINALS, PETER.

12:32.168 --> 12:33.499
SENTIMENTAL...

12:33.586 --> 12:35.497
SOFT!

12:35.588 --> 12:40.003
AND VERY PREOCCUPIED
WITH MY BROTHER.

12:43.721 --> 12:47.680
I SHOULD CLOSE THE DOOR ON YOU.

12:47.767 --> 12:50.099
PERHAPS THIS IS MY SICKNESS.

12:50.186 --> 12:52.678
'ZZZ

12:52.772 --> 12:56.106
I ONLY SEE THE BOY...

12:56.192 --> 12:57.478
NOT THE MAN.

12:59.779 --> 13:01.520
SLEEP ON THE COUCH.

13:01.614 --> 13:05.107
LOOK. WHY DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND?

13:05.201 --> 13:07.909
YOU'RE LIKE A FATHER.

13:07.996 --> 13:10.454
YOU'RE THE ONLY THING IN
THE WORLD THAT I'VE EVER LOVED.

13:10.540 --> 13:13.032
WHAT HAVE I EVER HAD TO LOVE?

13:13.126 --> 13:14.992
WHAT?

13:15.086 --> 13:18.545
A DRUNKEN FATHER VVHO USED TO
SLAM ME AGAINST THE VVALL?

13:18.631 --> 13:21.293
AN OLD LADY...

13:21.384 --> 13:24.718
WHO HAD NO MARBLES IN HER HEAD?

13:24.804 --> 13:27.592
SHE DIDN'T EVEN RECOGNIZE ME
HALF THE TIME.

13:27.682 --> 13:31.926
THAT'S WHY I USED
TO COME HERE, BECAUSE...

13:32.020 --> 13:34.728
BECAUSE YOU WERE GENTLE WITH ME,
AND YOU TALKED TO ME,

13:34.814 --> 13:36.805
AND YOU FEED ME.
AND YOU TOOK CARE OF ME.

13:38.818 --> 13:41.355
ERNST...

13:41.446 --> 13:43.153
ERNST, YOU'RE MY FATHER.

13:46.034 --> 13:48.275
THAT'S THE BOY AGAIN SPEAKING.

13:50.830 --> 13:53.663
THE LITTLE BOY
WITH SO MUCH FEAR IN HIM.

13:57.253 --> 13:58.618
REST.

13:58.713 --> 14:00.954
REST WELL.

14:34.874 --> 14:36.205
WHO'S OUT THERE?

14:36.292 --> 14:38.329
WHO IS IT?

14:38.419 --> 14:40.626
[in German accent]:
A FRIEND, MR. VOLLMER.

14:40.713 --> 14:42.420
A FRIEND?

14:42.507 --> 14:45.420
YOU HAVE
NEED OF FRIENDS, ALLIES.

14:45.510 --> 14:47.717
COME DOWN, MR. VOLLMER.

14:47.804 --> 14:50.387
COME DOWN,
AND WE WILL TALK, YOU AND I.

14:58.731 --> 15:01.644
HELLO, MR. VOLLMER.

15:01.734 --> 15:05.318
WHO ARE YOU?
HOW DID YOU KNOW WHERE I WAS?

15:05.405 --> 15:07.237
<i>[laughs]</i>

15:07.323 --> 15:10.065
I SIMPLY FOLLOWED YOUR TEARS,
MR. VOLLMER.

15:11.869 --> 15:14.247
YOU SAID THAT YOU HAD SOMETHING
TO TALK ABOUT.

15:14.330 --> 15:16.537
I DO, I DO INDEED.

15:16.624 --> 15:20.162
I HAVE YOU TO TALK ABOUT,
AND THE THINGS YOU BELIEVE IN,

15:20.253 --> 15:22.995
WHICH ARE THE THINGS
/BELIEVE IN, AS WELL.

15:23.089 --> 15:26.673
YOUR SUCCESS, MR. VOLLMER,
WILL BE MYSUCCESS.

15:26.759 --> 15:28.375
GO ON.

15:28.469 --> 15:29.925
GOOD.

15:30.012 --> 15:32.595
LET US START BY YOUR LEARNING

15:32.640 --> 15:36.474
WHAT ARE THE DYNAMICS
OF A CROWD.

15:36.561 --> 15:39.053
HOW DO YOU MOVE A MOB,
MR. VOLLMER?

15:39.147 --> 15:40.854
HOW DO YOU EXCITE THEM?

15:40.940 --> 15:43.272
HOW DO YOU MAKE THEM FEEL
AS ONE WITH YOU?

15:43.359 --> 15:46.477
L-| DON'T KNOW. HOW?

15:46.571 --> 15:48.187
JOIN THEM FIRST, MR. VOLLMER.

15:48.281 --> 15:49.521
JOIN THEM?

15:49.615 --> 15:52.323
YES, WHEN YOU SPEAK TO THEM,

15:52.410 --> 15:55.493
SPEAK TO THEM AS IF YOU
WERE A MEMBER OF THE MOB.

15:55.580 --> 16:00.074
SPEAK TO THEM IN THEIR LANGUAGE,
ON THEIR LEVEL.

16:00.168 --> 16:02.159
<i>MAKE THEIR HATE YOUR HATE.</i>

16:02.253 --> 16:06.713
IF THEY ARE POOR,
TALK TO THEM OF POVERTY.

16:06.799 --> 16:10.508
IF THEY ARE AFRAID,
TALK TO THEM OF THEIR FEARS.

16:10.595 --> 16:12.882
AND IF THEY ARE ANGRY,
MR. VOLLMER,

16:12.972 --> 16:14.883
IF THEY ARE ANGRY,

16:14.974 --> 16:17.261
GIVE THEM OBJECTS
FOR THEIR ANGER.

16:17.351 --> 16:19.308
BUT MOST OF ALL,

16:19.395 --> 16:22.513
THE THING THAT IS MOST
OF THE ESSENCE, MR. VOLLMER,

16:22.607 --> 16:26.396
IS THAT YOU MAKE THIS MOB
AN EXTENSION OF YOURSELF.

16:26.486 --> 16:30.104
SAY TO THEM THINGS LIKE...

16:30.198 --> 16:33.111
THINGS LIKE...

16:33.201 --> 16:35.533
"THEY CALL US HATEMONGERS.

16:35.620 --> 16:38.112
"THEY SAY WE'RE PREJUDICED.

16:38.206 --> 16:39.867
"THEY SAY WE'RE BIASED.

16:39.957 --> 16:44.747
"THEY SAY WE HATE
MINORITIES-- MINORITIES.

16:44.837 --> 16:47.329
"UNDERSTAND
THE TERM, NEIGHBORS:

16:47.423 --> 16:50.006
"MINORITIES.

16:50.092 --> 16:53.335
"SHOULD I TELL YOU
WHO ARE THE MINORITIES?

16:53.429 --> 16:55.340
"SHOULD I TELL YOU?

16:55.431 --> 16:56.933
IIWE__,!

16:57.016 --> 16:59.303
WE ARE THE MINORITIES!"

17:01.229 --> 17:04.142
THAT WAY, MR. VOLLMER.

17:04.232 --> 17:06.314
START IT THAT WAY.

17:08.653 --> 17:11.566
I... UNDERSTAND.

17:11.656 --> 17:13.818
I THINK I UNDERSTAND.

17:17.036 --> 17:18.652
[weakly]: NEIGHBORS...

17:21.249 --> 17:23.115
<i>[more confidently]: N E I G H B O <i>RS.</i></i>

17:25.377 --> 17:27.164
THEY CALL US...

17:27.255 --> 17:28.871
HATEMONGERS.

17:30.258 --> 17:33.046
THEY SAY...

17:33.135 --> 17:34.842
<i>[even more confidently]:
WE'RE PREJUDICED.</i>

17:36.597 --> 17:39.464
THEY SAY...

17:39.559 --> 17:41.971
<i>WE'RE BIASED!</i>

17:42.061 --> 17:47.306
THEY SAY
THAT WE HATE THE MINORITIES!

17:47.400 --> 17:49.892
THE MINORITIES.

17:49.986 --> 17:53.195
UNDERSTAND THE TERM, NEIGHBORS.

17:53.281 --> 17:56.148
THE MINORITIES.

17:56.242 --> 18:00.611
SHALL I TELL YOU
WHO THE MINORITIES ARE?!

18:00.705 --> 18:02.616
WE, WE, WE...!

18:02.707 --> 18:05.290
WE ARE THE MINORITIES!

18:05.376 --> 18:10.416
BECAUSE PATRIOTISM...

18:10.506 --> 18:12.838
IS A MINORITY.

18:12.925 --> 18:15.633
BECAUSE LOVE OF COUNTRY...

18:15.720 --> 18:18.087
IS THE MINORITY.

18:18.180 --> 18:22.845
BECAUSE TO LIVE
IN A FREE, WHITE AMERICA

18:22.935 --> 18:26.553
SEEMS TO BE
OF A MINORITY OPINION!

18:26.647 --> 18:30.436
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING,
NEIGHBORS.

18:30.526 --> 18:32.437
I WANT YOU TO DWELL ON THIS,

18:32.528 --> 18:35.441
JUST DWELL ON IT.

18:35.531 --> 18:40.446
WE HAD THE ATOM BOMB,

18:40.536 --> 18:43.528
AND SUDDENLY...

18:43.623 --> 18:46.240
THE RUSSIANS HAD IT.

18:46.334 --> 18:51.454
WE WANTED
TO SEND MEN INTO SPACE!

18:51.547 --> 18:57.168
BUT IT WAS THE RUSSIANS
WHO GOT THERE FIRST!

18:57.261 --> 18:59.753
WE HAD THE HYDROGEN BOMB!

19:02.975 --> 19:08.266
IT WAS THE RUSSIANS
WHO EXPLODED THEIRS.

19:08.356 --> 19:11.690
WHO GAVE THEM THE BOMBS?

19:11.776 --> 19:16.145
WHO SOLD US OUT?
WHO STABBED US IN THE BACK?

19:16.238 --> 19:18.900
WELL...

19:18.991 --> 19:21.699
IF IT'S A MINORITY OPINION

19:21.786 --> 19:25.074
THAT WE HAVE TO SURVIVE,

19:25.164 --> 19:29.123
THEN WE ARE THE MINORITY.

19:29.210 --> 19:31.747
AND THIS MINORITY

19:31.837 --> 19:33.703
WILL NOT STOP

19:33.798 --> 19:37.041
UNTIL IT IS THE MAJORITY!

19:37.134 --> 19:41.503
THIS MINORITY
WILL NOT GIVE UP THE FIGHT!

19:41.597 --> 19:44.931
THIS... IS THE PROMISE

19:45.017 --> 19:48.100
AND THIS, THIS IS THE LEGACY!

19:48.187 --> 19:53.182
<i>[applause and cheers]</i>

19:58.406 --> 20:01.239
[applause and cheers]

20:05.413 --> 20:09.748
PAL, WE'RE IN THERE NOW, HUH?
NO MORE STREET CORNERS?

20:09.834 --> 20:12.542
OH, BOY,
ARE WE GOING NOW, HUH?

20:12.628 --> 20:13.959
CONGRATULATIONS.

20:14.046 --> 20:15.332
CONGRATULATIONS.
THANKS.

20:15.423 --> 20:17.915
- NICE SPEECH.
- THANK YOU.

20:20.636 --> 20:23.549
LOOK, I'M NOT GONNA WAIT
MUCH LONGER, YOU UNDERSTAND?

20:23.639 --> 20:25.300
IF I DON'T GET PAID,
YOU DON'T HAVE THE HALL

20:25.391 --> 20:27.553
- TOMORROW NIGHT.
- GIBBONS, WILL YOU COOL IT?!

20:27.643 --> 20:29.350
CAN'T YOU SEE WE'RE BUSY?

20:29.437 --> 20:32.145
LOOK, I'M NOT GONNA WAIT
ANOTHER FIVE MINUTES!

20:32.231 --> 20:34.563
I WANT IT SETTLED NOW.
I TOLD YOU,

20:34.650 --> 20:36.266
NO DOUGH, NO RENTAL.

20:36.360 --> 20:38.397
NO DOUGH, NO USE OF THE HALL
TOMORROW NIGHT.

20:38.487 --> 20:40.774
I'M NOT RUNNING THIS PLACE
JUST FOR PLEASURE.

20:40.865 --> 20:43.027
WHAT SEEMS TO BE THE PROBLEM?

20:43.117 --> 20:45.233
THIS IS A VERY HUNGRY MAN HERE.

20:45.327 --> 20:47.113
HE GOT TO HAVE HIS SHEKELS,

20:47.204 --> 20:48.990
GOT TO HAVE HIS
LITTLE OLD MONEY.

20:49.081 --> 20:52.574
I TOLD YOU GUYS YOU VVERE
THREE VVEEKS BACK IN RENT.

20:52.668 --> 20:54.534
YOU SAID YOU'D
GIVE ME IT A WEEK AGO.

20:54.628 --> 20:57.165
AND ALL I DID GET WAS
CIGARETTE BUTTS ON THE FLOOR.

20:57.256 --> 21:00.374
AM I TO UNDERSTAND THAT YOU'RE
GONNA LOCK US OUT OF THIS HALL

21:00.468 --> 21:02.254
BECAUSE OF A COUPLE WEEKS' RENT?

21:02.344 --> 21:05.006
YOU UNDERSTAND RIGHT.

21:05.097 --> 21:07.885
$200 DUE,
$200 THAT I AIN'T RECEIVED.

21:07.975 --> 21:11.809
WE HAPPEN TO BE
A YOUNG MOVEMENT.

21:11.896 --> 21:15.355
WE'RE STILL STRUGGLING.
WE NEED TIME TO GROW.

21:15.441 --> 21:17.773
BUT I DON'T RENT TIME--

21:17.860 --> 21:20.397
I JUST RENT THE HALL.

21:20.488 --> 21:21.978
IT'S THE MONEY

21:22.072 --> 21:25.610
OR YOU BUILD A PLATFORM
IN THE STREET.

21:34.502 --> 21:36.243
WHEW.

21:36.337 --> 21:39.045
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO, PETE?
WE GOT TO DO SOMETHING.

21:39.131 --> 21:41.623
I DON'T SEE WHY WE WALK
TIPTOE WITH THIS GUY.

21:41.717 --> 21:44.129
WHY DON'T I EDUCATE HIM?
I CAN DO IT.

21:44.220 --> 21:45.836
- I GUARANTEE IT.
- YEAH.

21:45.930 --> 21:48.012
- SOMEBODY LEFT THIS FOR YOU.
- WHO?

21:48.098 --> 21:50.556
NOBODY SAW HIM.
IT WAS LEFT AT THE BACK DOOR

21:50.643 --> 21:53.226
YOUR NAME IS ON IT.

21:53.312 --> 21:55.178
TWO C's!

21:55.272 --> 21:58.060
HEY, HOW ABOUT THAT, HUH?
WE NEEDED 200 BUCKS' FOR RENT,

21:58.150 --> 22:00.232
AND THERE IT IS!

22:00.319 --> 22:02.651
- DID YOU SEE WHO LEFT THIS?
- NO, I DIDN'T.

22:02.738 --> 22:05.355
THE MESSAGE WAS JUST
FOR YOU TO GET IT, THAT'S ALL.

22:07.743 --> 22:09.734
GIBBONS, COME AND GET IT.

22:30.683 --> 22:33.300
<i>[laughing]</i>

22:37.356 --> 22:40.348
WHERE'D THE DOUGH COME FROM?
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA?

22:42.570 --> 22:44.902
YOU WERE GREAT TONIGHT, PETE.

22:44.989 --> 22:47.276
YOU WERE REALLY SOMETHING.

22:47.366 --> 22:50.904
I CAN'T DESCRIBE HOW IT SOUNDED.

22:50.995 --> 22:53.362
YOU HAD THEM...

22:53.414 --> 22:55.200
JUST LIKE THAT, YOU HAD THEM.

22:57.376 --> 22:59.367
WE'RE GONNA MAKE IT NOW, FRANK.

23:06.385 --> 23:08.501
NOW WE'RE <i>REALLY</i>
GOING TO MAKE IT.

23:08.596 --> 23:11.008
YOU BET YOUR LIFE.

23:32.828 --> 23:35.320
AN EXCELLENT PERFORMANCE,
MR. VOLLMER.

23:35.414 --> 23:36.745
VERY EFFECTIVE.

23:36.832 --> 23:39.199
YOU LEARN QUICKLY.

23:40.836 --> 23:42.338
THANK YOU.

23:42.421 --> 23:44.537
I'D LIKE TO KNOW
WHO I'M THANKING.

23:44.632 --> 23:46.964
IT DOES NOT MAKE
VERY MUCH DIFFERENCE.

23:47.051 --> 23:49.759
I AM JUST PLEASED I COULD HELP.

23:49.803 --> 23:51.965
YOU LEARNED THE STYLE VERY WELL.

23:52.056 --> 23:55.048
YOU DELIVERED THE SPEECH
EXACTLY AS I TOLD YOU.

23:55.142 --> 23:57.975
I'M VERY OBLIGED.

23:58.062 --> 23:59.769
THE MONEY?

23:59.855 --> 24:01.812
OH, IT WAS THE LEAST I COULD DO.

24:01.899 --> 24:05.767
WE COULD NOT VERY WELL HAVE YOU
THROWN OUT INTO THE STREETS.

24:05.861 --> 24:09.149
I HAPPEN TO FEEL YOUR WORK
IS VERY IMPORTANT.

24:09.239 --> 24:11.196
ARE YOU ONE OF US?

24:11.283 --> 24:12.990
ONE OF <i>YOU,</i> MR. VOLLMER?

24:13.077 --> 24:15.193
YOU MIGHT SAY I AM YOU.

24:15.287 --> 24:18.370
NOW, I HAVE SOME SUGGESTIONS.

24:18.457 --> 24:21.415
IWILL CONTINUE
TO GIVE YOU ADVICE.

24:21.502 --> 24:23.789
BUT THERE IS A MATTER
OF GREAT IMPORTANCE

24:23.879 --> 24:25.461
THAT MUST BE TAKEN CARE OF.

24:25.547 --> 24:27.800
WHAT IS IT?

24:27.883 --> 24:30.215
AN EXPEDIENT, MR. VOLLMER.

24:30.302 --> 24:32.464
OH, YOU MIGHT CALL IT A, UH...

24:32.554 --> 24:34.215
<i>A CAUSE CELEBRE.</i>

24:34.306 --> 24:38.766
SOMETHING TO CEMENT
THE ORGANIZATION TOGETHER.

24:38.852 --> 24:42.095
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
- A MARTYR.

24:42.189 --> 24:45.147
THE ORGANIZATION NEEDS A MARTYR.

24:45.234 --> 24:47.316
A MARTYR?
HOW DO YOU FIND A MARTYR?

24:47.403 --> 24:50.236
YOU DO NOT <i>FIND</i> ONE,
MR. VOLLMER.

24:50.322 --> 24:52.814
<i>YOU CHOOSE</i> ONE.

24:52.908 --> 24:56.401
YOU TAKE ONE OF NO VALUE,
AND YOU MAKE HIM INTO A SYMBOL.

24:56.495 --> 24:59.032
YOU WRAP HIM IN A FLAG,

24:59.123 --> 25:02.241
AND YOU MAKE HIS DEATH
WORK FOR YOU.

25:02.334 --> 25:07.044
FIND A MAN VVHO IS OF NO
VALUE VVHILE HE'S ALl\/E

25:07.131 --> 25:09.247
BUT WHO CAN SERVE YOU
WHEN HE'S DEAD.

25:09.341 --> 25:10.923
IS THERE SUCH A ONE?

25:11.010 --> 25:14.253
<i>[footsteps approaching]</i>

25:14.346 --> 25:17.805
- WE'RE WAITING, PETE.
- I'LL BE RIGHT THERE, NICK.

25:17.891 --> 25:18.551
SURE, PETE.

25:22.813 --> 25:26.272
YOU TALKING TO SOMEBODY, PETE?

25:26.358 --> 25:29.271
YOU TELL FRANK TO COME IN HERE.

25:29.361 --> 25:31.102
ALONE.

25:31.196 --> 25:33.278
SURE THING, PETE.

25:33.365 --> 25:34.742
RIGHT AWAY.

25:38.996 --> 25:40.532
EXCELLENT, MR. VOLLMER.

25:40.622 --> 25:42.158
AN EXCELLENT CHOICE.

25:43.542 --> 25:46.284
I WAS JUST THINKING...

25:46.378 --> 25:48.870
THERE MUST BE SOME OTHER WAY.

25:48.964 --> 25:50.625
ANOTHER WAY?

25:50.716 --> 25:53.003
THERE IS <i>NO</i> OTHER
WAY, MR. VOLLMER.

25:53.093 --> 25:55.084
AND IF YOU SOFTEN UP,

25:55.179 --> 25:57.295
IF YOU WEAKEN NOW,

25:57.389 --> 26:00.131
THERE IS NO POINT IN GOING ON.

26:00.225 --> 26:01.477
NOW...

26:01.560 --> 26:03.301
WHEN FRANK COMES BACK,

26:03.395 --> 26:06.478
TELL HIM YOU HAVE
DISCOVERED AN INFORMER.

26:06.565 --> 26:11.105
TELL HIM THE INFORMER HAS
DONE YOU IRREPARABLE DAMAGE.

26:11.195 --> 26:14.563
TELL HIM THE INFORMER
MUST BE PUT OUT OF THE WAY.

26:14.656 --> 26:16.397
BUT...

26:16.492 --> 26:19.484
PUT OUT OF THE WAY
CLEVERLY, MR. VOLLMER.

26:19.578 --> 26:22.115
PUT OUT OF THE WAY SUBTLEY.

26:22.206 --> 26:25.494
PUT OUT OF THE WAY
SO THAT THERE IS SOME QUESTION

26:25.584 --> 26:27.370
AS TO WHO IS RESPONSIBLE.

26:30.172 --> 26:32.960
NICK'S, UH, BEEN WITH US
FROM THE BEGINNING.

26:33.050 --> 26:34.916
FROM THE BEGINNING?

26:35.010 --> 26:37.126
OH, NO, MR. VOLLMER.

26:37.221 --> 26:39.303
NONE OF YOU WERE THERE
AT THE BEGINNING.

26:39.389 --> 26:40.550
NONE OF YOU.

26:40.641 --> 26:43.724
NICK'S A FRIEND OF MINE.

26:43.811 --> 26:46.724
THIS IS AN ACT OF FRIENDSHIP.

26:46.814 --> 26:49.431
WE ARE ALLOWING HIM
TO SERVE THE CAUSE.

26:49.525 --> 26:51.937
<i>[footsteps approaching]</i>

26:52.027 --> 26:55.520
NICK SAID YOU
WANTED TO SEE ME.

26:55.614 --> 26:57.946
WE'VE GOT A STOOLIE
IN THE GROUP, FRANK.

26:58.033 --> 27:00.525
A STOOLIE?

27:00.619 --> 27:01.825
NICK.

27:04.248 --> 27:05.784
NICK'S BEEN TALKING.

27:05.874 --> 27:07.660
I THINK HE'S BEEN
HIRED BY THE POLICE.

27:07.751 --> 27:09.742
NICK?!
NICK HAS DONE THAT?

27:11.463 --> 27:13.625
I KNOW IT FOR A FACT.

27:13.715 --> 27:16.377
EVERYTHING WE'VE DONE
AND EVERYTHING WE'VE SAID...

27:16.468 --> 27:17.924
NICK'S TOLD.

27:18.011 --> 27:19.922
WHAT DO WE DO, PETE?

27:20.013 --> 27:22.004
GET RID OF HIM.
GET RID OF HIM.

27:22.099 --> 27:25.558
MAKE IT LOOK LIKE
SOMEBODY ELSE DID IT.

27:25.644 --> 27:29.387
MAKE IT LOOK LIKE SOMEBODY
WHO HATES US DID IT.

27:29.481 --> 27:31.392
I UNDERSTAND.

27:31.483 --> 27:33.474
I UNDERSTAND, PETE.

27:33.569 --> 27:35.310
YOU CALL IT...

27:35.362 --> 27:37.069
YOU'VE GOT IT.

27:56.884 --> 27:58.921
[sirens sounding]

28:20.908 --> 28:24.026
CROSS OFF THE FAT ONE.

28:24.119 --> 28:27.032
ANYTHING ELSE?

28:27.122 --> 28:28.533
RIGHT.

28:45.724 --> 28:48.136
WE NOW, ALL OF US,
HAVE A MARTYR.

28:53.357 --> 28:56.395
WE HAVE A MARTYR!

29:09.164 --> 29:12.998
Announcen <i>TWILIGHT ZONE I/V/LL CONTINUE
AFTER STA T/ON lDENT/F/CA T/ON.</i>

29:48.412 --> 29:50.779
- IT'S A GOOD CROWD.
- RIGHT UP TO THE CEILING.

29:54.418 --> 29:57.536
WHAT'S THE MATTER, STANLEY?

29:57.629 --> 29:59.085
IT'S NOTHING, PETE.

29:59.172 --> 30:01.504
- THEN WHY THE LOOK?
- IT'S NOTHING,

30:01.591 --> 30:03.582
IT'S NOTHING AT ALL.

30:03.677 --> 30:06.465
AH, NOW, COME ON.
YOU CAN TELL ME, STANLEY.

30:06.555 --> 30:08.341
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

30:08.432 --> 30:11.766
NICK WAS MY FRIEND, PETE.
HE WAS A NICE GUY.

30:11.852 --> 30:13.934
I MISS HIM.

30:14.021 --> 30:16.479
DO YOU WANT ME TO REALLY
TELL YOU WHAT NICK WAS?

30:20.819 --> 30:22.810
WOULD YOU REALLY LIKE
A RUNDOWN?

30:22.904 --> 30:26.488
HE WAS A FAT PIG!

30:26.575 --> 30:28.065
WITH NO GUTS.

30:28.160 --> 30:30.948
HE WAS A GREASY BIGMOUTH

30:31.038 --> 30:33.746
WHO COPPED OUT AT EVERY TURN.

30:33.832 --> 30:36.164
HE WAS A NICKEL-AND-DIME
JUDAS,

30:36.251 --> 30:38.663
AND HE GOT EXACTLY
WHAT HE DESERVED.

30:38.754 --> 30:42.167
SO DON'T MOURN FOR NICK.

30:42.257 --> 30:44.214
BECAUSE HE DOESN'T
RATE MOURNING--

30:44.301 --> 30:46.292
NOT THAT PIG.

31:00.359 --> 31:03.351
[whistles and cheers]

31:11.411 --> 31:16.372
A MAN OF HONOR DIED LAST WEEK.

31:16.458 --> 31:20.793
A DECENT, COURAGEOUS FIGHTER

31:20.879 --> 31:24.622
FOR THE CAUSE OF FREEDOM

31:24.716 --> 31:26.502
GAVE HIS LIFE.

31:26.593 --> 31:30.382
HE GAVE HIS LIFE FOR US!

31:30.472 --> 31:34.807
SOME SKULKING... ASSASSIN

31:34.893 --> 31:38.636
MURDERED HIM!

31:38.730 --> 31:40.471
BUT FRIENDS,

31:40.565 --> 31:42.226
AND NEIGHBORS,

31:42.317 --> 31:45.400
AND CO-FIGHTERS...

31:45.445 --> 31:50.906
NICK BLOSS DID NOT DIE IN VAIN.

31:50.992 --> 31:55.452
THEY STILLED HIS GREAT HEART...

31:55.539 --> 32:00.579
BUT THEY COULD NOT
STIFLE HIS MEMORY.

32:00.669 --> 32:03.081
THEY COULD NOT...

32:03.171 --> 32:06.584
OBLITERATE HIS COURAGE.

32:06.675 --> 32:09.087
THEY COULD NOT...

32:09.177 --> 32:11.794
WIPE AWAY HIS HONOR.

32:11.888 --> 32:14.266
HE LIVES IN YOU,

32:14.349 --> 32:17.057
AND HE LIVES IN ME.

32:17.144 --> 32:19.511
HE LIVES DEEP IN THE GUT

32:19.604 --> 32:21.561
OF EVERY HUMAN BEING

32:21.648 --> 32:23.150
WHO WANTS TO SEE

32:23.233 --> 32:26.271
THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
BE FREE.

32:26.361 --> 32:28.693
NICK BLOSS

32:28.780 --> 32:32.068
DIED FOR THIS.

32:32.159 --> 32:36.278
AND YOU AND I...

32:36.371 --> 32:41.537
WE MUST LIVE FOR THIS!

32:41.626 --> 32:44.493
[cheers and whistles]

32:44.588 --> 32:48.081
\/ollmer: ...AND LET
SOMEBODYELSE CONCERN THEMSELVES

32:48.175 --> 32:50.382
WITH THE LIFEBLOOD
OF A NATION...

32:50.469 --> 32:52.881
HE'S GOT A VOICE ON HIM.

32:55.974 --> 32:59.308
I KNEW IT
WHEN IT WAS JUST A WHIMPER.

32:59.394 --> 33:01.510
THAT'S A BAD KID, THAT ONE.

33:01.605 --> 33:05.314
USED TO BE, USED TO BE
PEOPLE WOULD LAUGH AT HIM.

33:05.400 --> 33:08.108
BUT LATELY,
HE GETS THE CROWDS,

33:08.195 --> 33:11.108
AND NOT MANY PEOPLE
LAUGH EITHER.

33:11.198 --> 33:13.314
YOU'VE KNOW HIM
A LONG TIME, HAVEN'T YOU?

33:13.408 --> 33:15.900
SINCE HE WAS A CHILD.

33:15.994 --> 33:18.736
A SILENT, LITTLE BOY
WITH VERY LITTLE TO SAY.

33:18.830 --> 33:22.789
<i>[Vollmer continues orating
in background]</i>

33:22.876 --> 33:25.743
\/ollmer: WE'RE OVERDUE TO
CUT AWAY THE CANCEROUS...

33:25.837 --> 33:28.920
I'VE SEEN IT BEFORE.

33:29.007 --> 33:31.590
I'VE SEEN IT ALL BEFORE.

33:31.676 --> 33:34.714
THAT WAS ANOTHER TIME, MR. GANZ.

33:34.804 --> 33:38.297
ANOTHER PLACE,
ANOTHER KIND OF PEOPLE.

33:38.391 --> 33:40.553
THAT DOESN'T GO HERE.

33:40.644 --> 33:45.354
AND THAT'S WHAT WE SAID, TOO,
THEY WERE BROWN SCUM.

33:45.440 --> 33:49.775
TEMPORARY INSANITY,
PART OF THE PASSING SCENE...

33:49.861 --> 33:53.729
TOO MONSTROUS TO BE REAL.

33:53.823 --> 33:56.952
SO, WE IGNORED THEM

33:57.035 --> 33:59.402
OR LAUGHED AT THEM.

33:59.496 --> 34:01.362
<i>BECAUSE WE COULDN'T BELIEVE</i>

34:01.456 --> 34:03.367
THAT THERE WERE ENOUGH
INSANE PEOPLE

34:03.458 --> 34:07.372
TO WALK ALONGSIDE OF THEM.

34:07.462 --> 34:09.373
[sighs]

34:09.464 --> 34:11.956
AND THEN ONE MORNING,

34:12.050 --> 34:15.384
THE COUNTRY WOKE UP
FROM AN UNEASY SLEEP...

34:15.469 --> 34:17.962
<i>[Vollmer continues orating
in background]</i>

34:18.056 --> 34:19.888
...AND THERE
WAS NO MORE LAUGHTER.

34:23.061 --> 34:26.975
THE PETER VOLLMERS
HAD TAKEN OVER.

34:27.065 --> 34:30.808
THE WILD ANIMALS HAD CHANGED
PLACES WITH US IN THE CAGE.

34:30.902 --> 34:33.768
\/ollmer: THIS NATION OF OURS
IS BEING BEATEN TO DEATH!

34:33.862 --> 34:36.855
JUST AS SURE AS THE ALMIGHTY

34:36.949 --> 34:39.987
MADE COMMUNISTS,
CATHOLICS, AND JEWS.

34:40.078 --> 34:42.570
THERE'S NO TIME TO STAND AROUND,

34:42.664 --> 34:44.996
SCRATCH OUR HEADS,
AND PULL OUR BEARDS,

34:45.083 --> 34:46.665
AND TWIDDLE WITH OUR EARLOBES...

34:46.751 --> 34:49.413
BUT NOT AGAIN.

34:49.504 --> 34:53.293
IT MUSTN'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

34:53.382 --> 34:55.215
WE CAN'T LET IT.

34:55.302 --> 34:59.421
WE SIMPLY CAN'T
LET IT HAPPEN AGAIN.

34:59.514 --> 35:01.596
ALL, ALL THAT NIGHTMARE.

35:01.683 --> 35:05.221
\/ollmer: ...\/lOLENCE HAPPENS TO
BE THE ONLY WAY TO BE VIOLENT...

35:05.312 --> 35:07.644
OH, NO...

35:07.731 --> 35:10.018
NO, NOT THIS TIME.

35:10.108 --> 35:12.725
\/ollmer: ...WE DO NOT
WANT TO BE PUSHED.

35:14.487 --> 35:17.024
NOW, I WANT TO ASK YOU
A FEW QUESTIONS.

35:17.115 --> 35:20.983
YOU JUST ANSWER YES OR NO
TO THE FOLLOWING.

35:21.077 --> 35:22.454
DO YOU WANT...

35:22.537 --> 35:25.450
THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA

35:25.498 --> 35:26.875
TO REMAIN FREE?

35:26.958 --> 35:29.245
All: YES!

35:29.336 --> 35:33.455
DO YOU WANT YOUR HOMES INFECTED

35:33.548 --> 35:37.291
WITH THE VERMIN
FROM FOREIGN SHORES?

35:37.385 --> 35:39.467
All: NO!

35:39.554 --> 35:43.468
NOW, LISTEN TO THIS ONE.

35:43.558 --> 35:47.301
DO YOU WANT
A BUNCH OF MONGRELS

35:47.395 --> 35:50.387
[crowd murmuring]
TO COME OVER HERE...

35:53.735 --> 35:56.102
GO ON, MR. VOLLMER.

35:56.196 --> 35:58.779
YOU WERE SAYING?

35:58.865 --> 36:03.075
I CAN TELL THEM
WHAT YOU WERE SAYING.

36:03.161 --> 36:05.698
I'VE HEARD IT BEFORE.

36:05.789 --> 36:08.907
I'VE HEARD IT
A THOUSAND TIMES BEFORE...

36:09.000 --> 36:11.913
IN MUNICH, IN BERLIN...

36:12.003 --> 36:15.496
ON A HUNDRED DIFFERENT
STREET CORNERS.

36:15.590 --> 36:18.082
IT WAS DRIVEL THEN,

36:18.176 --> 36:20.087
AND IT IS DRIVEL NOW.

36:20.178 --> 36:22.294
YOU'VE GOT TO STOP, ERNST.

36:22.389 --> 36:25.222
